Like a lot of people, I was trying to find a recipe that was like the soup at Olive Garden (don't scoff, food snobs--it's divine!). To make it approach the restaurant's version, take the suggestions from A Cook from Canastota. I doubled the recipe and browned 1 lb of ground beef instead of bacon and cooked the pasta separately and added it back in last. I also added more water, about 3-4 cups more. It definitely needs spicing up too: I added about 1 tb black pepper, 1 tsp white pepper, 1 tsp dried oregano, 1 tsp dried basil, and 2 tsp salt. Pretty darn close to OG's!

