I made this dish as printed the first time and found that it was missing a few little things. This time I made some modifications that made it a raving success at my dinner table. I used pancetta instead of bacon. It's a little bit expensive but you can't beat it for taste and texture. I also added 2 bay leaves, some fresh thyme and rosemary. I used the ditalini pasta and the cannellini beans but that's just a personal preference. I did have one major problem the first time I made this dish. I boiled the pasta in the soup and it soaked up all of the broth. This time I boiled the pasta separately and tossed the cooked pasta into the soup right before serving. The changes I made were strongly endorsed by my family who sampled the dish both ways.

